result.execSummary:
The defendant William Chucky Moseley was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operate w/o Valid License(3rd+ w/in3Yrs), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.05(3)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Costs Paid in Full - Balance of bond has been refunded to the Poster.
Good Time Credit and Huber Privileges granted.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

records.addlTxt: Case Called @ 3:47 PM: Defendant William Chucky Moseley in court, appearing pro se.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Def does not wish counsel today and is prepared to resolve the matter with a GP.   Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea (No DL 3):  GP  Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  Upon motion of the State, 16TR-862 and 16TR-863 DRI.  ADA recommends guidelines for a 3rd offense.  Statement by Def:  None offered.  The Court:  Orders 10 days WCJ, GT and Huber, No TS credit, Report:  6/1/2016 at 8:00 PM - Court Costs - Bond to Apply - 60 DTP any Bal or PP.  DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.  Appeal Rights Given.
